24:T490,{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"INCOTERMS 2020 for Commodity Buyers: FOB vs CIF vs DAP vs DDP","description":"Understand FOB, CIF, DAP, and DDP INCOTERMS for industrial commodity procurement. Learn how delivery terms affect risk, cost, and logistics for crude oil, fuel, and agricultural supply contracts.","datePublished":"2026-06-23","dateModified":"2026-06-23","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"XRT Group","description":"XRT Group's commodity procurement team covering direct-origin sourcing, trade finance, inspection, logistics, and compliance across global supply chains.","url":"https://xrtgroup.com/about"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"XRT Group","logo":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://xrtgroup.com/xrt-mark.svg"}},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://xrtgroup.com/blog/incoterms-2020-explained-commodity-buyers"},"keywords":"INCOTERMS 2020, FOB commodity, CIF commodity, DAP supply chain, DDP procurement, commodity delivery terms, international commodity trade, procurement contracts","image":"https://xrtgroup.com/images/photo-lng-tanker-aerial.webp","articleSection":"PROCUREMENT"}25:T63c,{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Which INCOTERM is best for crude oil procurement?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"FOB is the most common term for crude oil procurement by industrial buyers with established tanker relationships. CIF is appropriate when the buyer needs the seller to arrange vessel and insurance due to operational constraints at origin."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Does INCOTERMS 2020 differ from INCOTERMS 2010?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Key changes in 2020 include: FCA now allows for on-board bills of lading under LC transactions; DPU replaces DAT; CIP now requires higher insurance coverage (Clause A) while CIF retains minimum Clause C coverage; FCA, DAP, DPU, and DDP now explicitly allow buyer